The paper presents a learning model that combines random forests and deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The model is designed for classification tasks and involves representation learning (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new pruning method to reduce redundant connections in the network (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents extensive experiments on different datasets, which suggests a focus on data science and machine learning (cs.DS).
